  "texts": [
    "In summary, we confirmed the potential of the few-shot NER model through GPT prompt engineering and found that providing similar examples rather than randomly sampled examples and informing tasks had a significant effect on performance improvement.",
    "In terms of the F1 score, few-shot learning with the GPT-3.5 ('text-davinci-003') model results in comparable MOR entity recognition performance as that of the SOTA model and improved DES recognition performance (Fig. 4c).",
    "In addition, we applied the same prompting strategy for GPT-4 model (gpt-4-0613), and obtained the improved performance in capturing MOR and DES entities.",
    "To explain how to extract answer to questions with GPT, we prepared battery device-related question answering dataset 22.",
    "Few-shot learning and fine-tuning of GPT models for extractive QA."
  ],
